OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1775070659
OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to woman killed
OL,4,Cafter driver 'fell asleep at wheel'
OL,6,FHer car subsequently burst into flames
OL,7,Fand, despite efforts of passers-by and
OL,8,Fparamedics to pull her from the
OL,9,Fburning car and give first aid, she
OL,10,Fwas pronounced dead at the scene.
OL,12,FPolice believe 32-year-old Kudrevicius
OL,13,Fhad fallen asleep at the wheel at the
OL,14,Ftime of the crash.
OL,16,FShinead's family paid tribute to the
OL,17,Fqualified HGV driver who they said
OL,18,Fwould refer to herself as "Mother
OL,19,FTrucker".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1775070659
OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to woman killed
OL,4,Cafter driver 'fell asleep at wheel'
OL,6,FThey said: "Her humour and sage advice
OL,7,Fsupported all around her, guiding both
OL,8,Ffriends and family through those dark
OL,9,Fperiods that we must now all bear
OL,10,Falone.
OL,12,F"We will miss her dancing, giggling,
OL,13,Fpositivity, her physical presence and
OL,14,Fher sense of fun.
OL,16,F"She had a love of penguins and had a
OL,17,Fcollection of cuddly ones in her room
OL,18,F` Christmas saw her place at the table
OL,19,Ftaken by one of her cuddly penguins."
OL,26,@nD@LOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1775070659
OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to woman killed
OL,4,Cafter driver 'fell asleep at wheel'
OL,6,FKudrevicius, from Quorn, was jailed
OL,7,Ffor four years and six months at
OL,8,FLincoln Crown Court on Friday after
OL,9,Fadmitting causing death by dangerous
OL,10,Fdriving. He was also banned from
OL,11,Fdriving for a total of seven years and
OL,12,Fthree months and must take an extended
OL,13,Fre-test before being allowed to drive
OL,14,Fagain.
OL,16,FLincolnshire Police said Kudrevicius
OL,17,Fhad never been able to explain why his
OL,18,FBMW veered onto the wrong side of the
OL,19,Froad when his hit Shinead's car,
OL,20,Fbelieving he was asleep at the time.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1775070659
OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to woman killed
OL,4,Cafter driver 'fell asleep at wheel'
OL,6,F"The importance of concentration and
OL,7,Fmaintaining proper lane discipline at
OL,8,Fall times cannot be overstated," Det
OL,9,FSgt Kate Johnston said.
OL,11,F"Before driving you should always
OL,12,Fensure you are well rested, as the
OL,13,Fplacing of your vehicle in an opposing
OL,14,Fcarriageway, particularly at night, is
OL,15,Fclearly dangerous and ultimately can
OL,16,Flead to tragic consequences, which
OL,17,FShinead's family must now live with."
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@eO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1775070659
OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to woman killed
OL,4,Cafter driver 'fell asleep at wheel'
OL,6,FShinead's family added: "We will never
OL,7,Fforget our beautiful Shinead, the one
OL,8,Fwho brought a breath of fresh air and
OL,9,Fa ray of sunshine to whomever she met.
OL,10,FEverywhere is now a duller, less
OL,11,Fcolourful place without her and the
OL,12,Fworld has lost one of those who was an
OL,13,Fembodiment of all that was good.
OL,15,F"Rest peacefully Shinead, you remain
OL,16,Fdeep inside our hearts and we will
OL,17,Flove you forever. Until we may all
OL,18,Fmeet again."
OL,26,@nD@YOUwD@AOUzD@LO]
